[2026-03-11T08:58:22Z] [unknown] n++{"conversation_id":"a165636b-6a19-49af-b3c9-370a7a786300","generation_id":"10a7b061-1e5d-453d-857c-30981d111605","model":"claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking","tool_name":"Read","tool_input":{"file_path":"g:\\trent_rules\\README.md"},"tool_output":"{\"file_path\":\"g:\\\\trent_rules\\\\README.md\",\"content_length\":29070}","duration":7.852,"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_017GAfRfySuvKNDufW3Xsf9L","hook_event_name":"postToolUse","cursor_version":"2.6.14","workspace_roots":["/g:/trent_rules"],"user_email":"obswrmartel3@gmail.com","transcript_path":"c:\\Users\\wrm3\\.cursor\\projects\\g-trent-rules\\agent-transcripts\\a165636b-6a19-49af-b3c9-370a7a786300\\a165636b-6a19-49af-b3c9-370a7a786300.jsonl"}

[2026-03-11T08:58:22Z] [unknown] n++{"conversation_id":"a165636b-6a19-49af-b3c9-370a7a786300","generation_id":"10a7b061-1e5d-453d-857c-30981d111605","model":"claude-4.6-sonnet-medium-thinking","file_path":"g:\\trent_rules\\README.md","edits":[{"old_string":"","new_string":"### Alternative: Windows Dynamic Links (Single Shared Storage)\n\nInstead of installing a full copy of trent into each project, you can use **Windows Dynamic Links** Gú— junction points that make every project folder point to your single `trent_rules` installation. Any edit to an agent, skill, or rule in one project is instantly reflected in all other projects.\n\n**When to use this approach:**\n- You work on many projects on the same Windows machine\n- You want agent/skill/rule updates to propagate everywhere immediately Gú— no re-installs\n- You're the primary developer and want a single source of truth for all trent configuration\n\n**How it works:**\n\nCopy `windows_dynamic_links.bat` (from the root of this repo) into your project folder and run it as Administrator. It creates Windows junction links for the four trent config directories:\n\n```\nyour-project/\nG—ÈG—úG—ú .agent     GÍó G:\\trent_rules\\.agent     (junction link)\nG—ÈG—úG—ú .claude    GÍó G:\\trent_rules\\.claude    (junction link)\nG—ÈG—úG—ú .cursor    GÍó G:\\trent_rules\\.cursor    (junction link)\nG——G—úG—ú .platforms GÍó G:\\trent_rules\\.platforms (junction link)\n```\n\nThe junction links behave exactly like real folders Gú— your IDE, git, and all tools see them as local directories. But writes go directly to `trent_rules`, so installing a new skill or editing a rule in any project updates the shared source immediately.\n\n**Steps:**\n\n```bat\nREM 1. Copy windows_dynamic_links.bat into your project folder\nREM 2. Open a terminal as Administrator\nREM 3. Navigate to your project folder\ncd C:\\path\\to\\your-project\n\nREM 4. Run the script\nwindows_dynamic_links.bat\n```\n\n**Before running**, open `windows_dynamic_links.bat` and verify the `SHARED` path matches where your `trent_rules` repo lives:\n\n```bat\nREM Edit this line to match your actual trent_rules location:\nset SHARED=G:\\trent_rules\n```\n\n> **Note:** Junction links are Windows-only (`mklink /J`). On Linux/Mac, use `ln -s` to create equivalent symbolic links. Junction links are not followed by git Gú— your project repo stays clean.\n\n**Trade-offs vs. standard install:**\n\n| | Standard Install (`trent_install`) | Dynamic Links |\n|---|---|---|\n| Updates | Re-run `trent_install` to get new agents/skills | Instant Gú— edits in any project apply everywhere |\n| Project isolation | Each project has its own copy | All projects share one copy |\n| Works on | All platforms | Windows only (junction links) |\n| Teammate compatibility | GÈÁ They get their own copy | GËŸ Only works on machines with same drive layout |\n\n---\n"}],"hook_event_name":"afterFileEdit","cursor_version":"2.6.14","workspace_roots":["/g:/trent_rules"],"user_email":"obswrmartel3@gmail.com","transcript_path":"c:\\Users\\wrm3\\.cursor\\projects\\g-trent-rules\\agent-transcripts\\a165636b-6a19-49af-b3c9-370a7a786300\\a165636b-6a19-49af-b3c9-370a7a786300.jsonl"}

